  "prompt": "Men: how would you like to be told by a woman that she is not interested? A guy is interested in me. He wants marriage but I want something casual.",
  "response": "Here are some suggestions for being direct but kind:\n\n1. Be clear and honest upfront\n- \"I'm looking for something casual, and it sounds like we want different things\"\n- \"I don't see a serious relationship or marriage happening between us\"\n\n2. Be respectful but firm\n- Don't give false hope\n- Don't make promises you can't keep\n- Be direct about your intentions\n\n3. Tone matters\n- Be kind but straightforward\n- Avoid being cruel or dismissive\n- Show you respect him as a person\n\n4. Potential script:\n\"I appreciate your interest, but I'm not looking for a serious relationship right now. I want to be clear that I'm only interested in something casual. If that doesn't work for you, I understand.\"\n\nMost men appreciate direct communication that doesn't waste their time or give false hope. Being honest prevents misunderstandings and potential hurt feelings later.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these points?",
